states practice--

00:11:44.435 --> 00:11:48.210 align:middle line:84%
a regular altered states
practice that both helps heal

00:11:48.210 --> 00:11:52.260 align:middle line:84%
the body, keeps us
grounded, helps balance

00:11:52.260 --> 00:11:54.560 align:middle line:84%
out other psychedelic
medicine use,

00:11:54.560 --> 00:11:56.720 align:middle line:84%
and it can be done
pretty regularly

00:11:56.720 --> 00:12:00.690 align:middle line:84%
to help clear that
psychic plaque that we

00:12:00.690 --> 00:12:07.320 align:middle line:84%
carry from day-to-day stress
and being rushed in the world.

00:12:07.320 --> 00:12:10.380 align:middle line:84%
>> These modalities are seen
most easily in the yogic

00:12:10.380 --> 00:12:13.690 align:middle line:84%
and Tibetan Buddhist
practices of the East.

00:12:13.690 --> 00:12:17.040 align:middle line:84%
Popularized in Western culture,
the core breath techniques

00:12:17.040 --> 00:12:21.180 align:middle line:84%
still remain in the highly
modernized forms of yoga today.

00:12:21.180 --> 00:12:24.300 align:middle line:10%
However, even newer
developments of using breath

00:12:24.300 --> 00:12:26.840 align:middle line:10%
to enhance health are seen
with Stig Severinsen's

00:12:26.840 --> 00:12:31.590 align:middle line:10%
"breatheology," Wim Hof's
"Innerfire," Buteyko breathing,

00:12:31.590 --> 00:12:33.720 align:middle line:10%
as well as many other
techniques for achieving

00:12:33.720 --> 00:12:35.950 align:middle line:10%
different outcomes.

00:12:35.950 --> 00:12:38.700 align:middle line:10%
The most popular of the
expanded states techniques

00:12:38.700 --> 00:12:40.710 align:middle line:10%
was developed by
Czech psychiatrist

00:12:40.710 --> 00:12:43.530 align:middle line:10%
and psychedelic
researcher Stanislav Grof

00:12:43.530 --> 00:12:45.870 align:middle line:10%
called holotropic breath.

00:12:45.870 --> 00:12:48.600 align:middle line:10%
After taking a break
from psychedelic studies,

00:12:48.600 --> 00:12:51.390 align:middle line:10%
he decided to write a few
books on the power of expanded

00:12:51.390 --> 00:12:53.650 align:middle line:10%
states of consciousness.

00:12:53.650 --> 00:12:58.610 align:middle line:10%
>> So I moved to Esalen,
and I was trading this house

00:12:58.610 --> 00:13:04.170 align:middle line:10%
and the food for workshops.

00:13:04.170 --> 00:13:07.710 align:middle line:84%
And I was basically
talking of what we found

00:13:07.710 --> 00:13:10.526 align:middle line:90%
in the psychedelic sessions.

00:13:10.526 --> 00:13:12.150 align:middle line:84%
And people were not
very happy with me.

00:13:12.150 --> 00:13:14.130 align:middle line:84%
They said, it's great
to hear about all

00:13:14.130 --> 00:13:16.890 align:middle line:84%
these great experiences,
but can't we do something?

00:13:16.890 --> 00:13:19.430 align:middle line:84%
Don't you have a little
stash on the side?

00:13:19.430 --> 00:13:23.350 align:middle line:84%
And I said, you know, I don't
have the license to do it.

00:13:23.350 --> 00:13:27.260 align:middle line:84%
And I think Esalen would
not be very happy with us.

00:13:27.260 --> 00:13:29.340 align:middle line:90%
But they kept asking.

00:13:29.340 --> 00:13:32.550 align:middle line:84%
So I started thinking
about what we could do.

00:13:32.550 --> 00:13:34.950 align:middle line:84%
We realized how much
can be achieved just

00:13:34.950 --> 00:13:37.200 align:middle line:84%
by such simple means
as breathing, music,

00:13:37.200 --> 00:13:39.210 align:middle line:90%
and the bodywork.

00:13:39.210 --> 00:13:41.610 align:middle line:84%
We were looking for a
good name, and we finally

00:13:41.610 --> 00:13:44.790 align:middle line:84%
came up with the name
holotropic because we

00:13:44.790 --> 00:13:48.320 align:middle line:84%
were seeing how this
experiential spectrum of people

00:13:48.320 --> 00:13:51.480 align:middle line:84%
is expanding from that
very constricted, limited

00:13:51.480 --> 00:13:54.210 align:middle line:84%
that is available in our
everyday consciousness.

00:13:54.210 --> 00:13:57.780 align:middle line:84%
So holos means whole, and
-trope or -troping means

00:13:57.780 --> 00:13:59.800 align:middle line:90%
moving towards.

00:13:59.800 --> 00:14:03.840 align:middle line:84%
Like in the name heliotrope,
is from helios, is the sun.

00:14:03.840 --> 00:14:07.740 align:middle line:84%
Heliotrope is the property of
the plant, the flower, always

00:14:07.740 --> 00:14:12.350 align:middle line:90%
oriented, going for the sun.

00:14:12.350 --> 00:14:15.130 align:middle line:84%
So it means moving
toward wholeness.

00:14:15.130 --> 00:14:18.030 align:middle line:84%
So holotropic states
are not like that.

00:14:18.030 --> 00:14:22.240 align:middle line:84%
Your intellectual functioning
is dramatically changed,

00:14:22.240 --> 00:14:23.490 align:middle line:90%
but not reduced.

00:14:23.490 --> 00:14:25.140 align:middle line:90%
It's transformed.

00:14:25.140 --> 00:14:27.470 align:middle line:84%
You can see certain
things much clearer.

00:14:27.470 --> 00:14:29.870 align:middle line:90%
You get insights about things.

00:14:29.870 --> 00:14:32.490 align:middle line:84%
Where you go inside,
and you find out

00:14:32.490 --> 00:14:36.430 align:middle line:84%
that the whole universe is
represented inside of your sky.

00:14:36.430 --> 00:14:38.460 align:middle line:84%
The whole universe
from this perspective

00:14:38.460 --> 00:14:40.980 align:middle line:90%
is coded somehow in the psyche.

00:14:40.980 --> 00:14:45.730 align:middle line:84%
It's available through
intrapsychic exploration.

00:14:45.730 --> 00:14:47.340 align:middle line:84%
And this is of
course the essence

00:14:47.340 --> 00:14:49.320 align:middle line:90%
of all the esoteric cultures.

00:14:49.320 --> 00:14:52.080 align:middle line:90%
As above, so below.

00:14:52.080 --> 00:14:54.130 align:middle line:90%
As without, so within.

00:14:54.130 --> 00:14:56.880 align:middle line:84%
So each individual
is a microcosm

00:14:56.880 --> 00:15:01.770 align:middle line:84%
that also contains
the whole macrocosm.

00:15:01.770 --> 00:15:04.980 align:middle line:84%
>> In a society hypnotized by
scientific study with the use

00:15:04.980 --> 00:15:08.790 align:middle line:84%
of external technologies,
exploration into the mysteries

00:15:08.790 --> 00:15:11.790 align:middle line:84%
of the universe using
self-observation is seen

00:15:11.790 --> 00:15:14.870 align:middle line:90%
as inaccurate and flimsy.

00:15:14.870 --> 00:15:18.740 align:middle line:84%
Answers to our most timely
questions, such as who am I?

00:15:18.740 --> 00:15:20.090 align:middle line:90%
Why am I here?

00:15:20.090 --> 00:15:21.600 align:middle line:90%
And, what am I to do?

00:15:21.600 --> 00:15:24.260 align:middle line:84%
Are given only the most
conservative answers like,

00:15:24.260 --> 00:15:25.370 align:middle line:90%
we don't know.

00:15:25.370 --> 00:15:27.650 align:middle line:84%
Or that gene hasn't
been found yet.

00:15:27.650 --> 00:15:30.050 align:middle line:90%
Speculation is frowned upon.

00:15:30.050 --> 00:15:32.150 align:middle line:84%
But psychedelic states
or natural highs

00:15:32.150 --> 00:15:35.330 align:middle line:84%
seem to push the mind
into greater curiosity,

00:15:35.330 --> 00:15:38.990 align:middle line:84%
expanded receptivity,
inner contemplation,

00:15:38.990 --> 00:15:40.850 align:middle line:90%
and wild speculation.

00:15:40.850 --> 00:15:44.330 align:middle line:84%
Those who seek altered
states of consciousness

00:15:44.330 --> 00:15:47.150 align:middle line:84%
are not doing so to
get more of the same.

00:15:47.150 --> 00:15:50.030 align:middle line:90%
They seek transformation.

00:15:50.030 --> 00:15:53.600 align:middle line:84%
People of all walks of life go
to the blazing hot and dry lake

00:15:53.600 --> 00:15:56.870 align:middle line:84%
bed of Black Rock City
for Burning Man one week

00:15:56.870 --> 00:15:58.310 align:middle line:90%
out of every year--

00:15:58.310 --> 00:16:01.280 align:middle line:84%
not to strengthen their
routines and habits,

00:16:01.280 --> 00:16:03.920 align:middle line:84%
but to dismantle them
and see beyond the veil

00:16:03.920 --> 00:16:05.810 align:middle line:90%
of their own making.

00:16:05.810 --> 00:16:08.930 align:middle line:10%
In a society touted as being
almost completely consumer

00:16:08.930 --> 00:16:14.030 align:middle line:10%
driven, people are left to use
plants, vacations, retreats,

00:16:14.030 --> 00:16:17.720 align:middle line:10%
natural, and unfortunately
not-so-natural substances

00:16:17.720 --> 00:16:21.100 align:middle line:10%
to shield their eyes and ears
from the onslaught of products

00:16:21.100 --> 00:16:24.250 align:middle line:10%
and sales gimmicks.

00:16:24.250 --> 00:16:27.000 align:middle line:10%
The Kogi people of
Columbia spend nine years

00:16:27.000 --> 00:16:29.100 align:middle line:10%
of their formative
life in darkness

00:16:29.100 --> 00:16:33.170 align:middle line:10%
in order to connect with what
they call cosmic consciousness.

00:16:33.170 --> 00:16:35.120 align:middle line:10%
Egyptians had the pyramids.

00:16:35.120 --> 00:16:37.380 align:middle line:10%
Romans used the catacombs.

00:16:37.380 --> 00:16:39.140 align:middle line:84%
And even the Essenes
in Israel are

00:16:39.140 --> 00:16:42.740 align:middle line:84%
reported to use extended
periods of darkness.

00:16:42.740 --> 00:16:46.070 align:middle line:84%
All of this to remove the
shackles of limited thinking

00:16:46.070 --> 00:16:49.460 align:middle line:84%
and liberate oneself from
the wheel of suffering.

00:16:49.460 --> 00:16:52.850 align:middle line:10%
John Chavez, author of
"Questions for the Lion Tamer,"

00:16:52.850 --> 00:16:55.220 align:middle line:10%
has pushed the speculative
envelope regarding

00:16:55.220 --> 00:16:59.420 align:middle line:10%
the role of indigenous DMT
and telepathy, lucid dreaming,

00:16:59.420 --> 00:17:02.750 align:middle line:10%
and the overall questions
of how much of our biology

00:17:02.750 --> 00:17:06.990 align:middle line:10%
we can actually control
through thoughts and actions.

00:17:06.990 --> 00:17:09.690 align:middle line:10%
Extended fasting leading
to years of inedia,

00:17:09.690 --> 00:17:13.140 align:middle line:10%
or living without food, breath
practice leading to world

00:17:13.140 --> 00:17:16.319 align:middle line:10%
records of 22 minutes
without oxygen,

00:17:16.319 --> 00:17:18.780 align:middle line:10%
breaking the four-minute
mile when doctors said it was

00:17:18.780 --> 00:17:22.319 align:middle line:10%
impossible, surviving
incurable diseases,

00:17:22.319 --> 00:17:25.950 align:middle line:10%
unbelievable feats of
strength and willpower,

00:17:25.950 --> 00:17:28.950 align:middle line:10%
all because the human
spirit seems to seek beyond

00:17:28.950 --> 00:17:34.840 align:middle line:10%
conventions and restrictions
and mostly with purpose--

00:17:34.840 --> 00:17:41.510 align:middle line:10%
to know thyself, not just
in theory but embodied.

00:17:41.510 --> 00:17:43.380 align:middle line:84%
The psychonauts
that long to witness

00:17:43.380 --> 00:17:45.650 align:middle line:84%
as much as they can on
this beautiful planet

00:17:45.650 --> 00:17:48.150 align:middle line:84%
in these amazingly
mysterious bodies

00:17:48.150 --> 00:17:50.520 align:middle line:84%
do so because the
greatest mystery of all

00:17:50.520 --> 00:17:53.580 align:middle line:84%
is right around the
corner, and this life

00:17:53.580 --> 00:17:56.300 align:middle line:90%
might be their only chance.

00:17:56.300 --> 00:17:59.510 align:middle line:84%
What truly lies on the other
shore when this body dies

00:17:59.510 --> 00:18:00.950 align:middle line:90%
is a mystery.

00:18:00.950 --> 00:18:02.510 align:middle line:84%
But glimpses into
that world have

00:18:02.510 --> 00:18:06.460 align:middle line:84%
been coming to light in the
form of near-death experiences.

00:18:06.460 --> 00:18:09.530 align:middle line:84%
And the experience is far
closer to a psychedelic journey

00:18:09.530 --> 00:18:11.790 align:middle line:90%
than one may think.

00:18:11.790 --> 00:18:14.600 align:middle line:10%
>> Michael Sabom, the
cardiologist who studied his

00:18:14.600 --> 00:18:19.100 align:middle line:10%
own patient-- he had a case
where they were operating

00:18:19.100 --> 00:18:22.670 align:middle line:10%
for a tumor which was sitting
at the base of the skull.

00:18:22.670 --> 00:18:25.410 align:middle line:90%
They had to freeze the patient.

00:18:25.410 --> 00:18:29.600 align:middle line:84%
So there was not only no
cardiogram showing anything,

00:18:29.600 --> 00:18:32.180 align:middle line:90%
but the EEG was flat.

00:18:32.180 --> 00:18:34.070 align:middle line:90%
There was no brain activity.

00:18:34.070 --> 00:18:38.450 align:middle line:10%
And yet from her they got
the most accurate perception

00:18:38.450 --> 00:18:41.060 align:middle line:10%
of this out of body perception.

00:18:41.060 --> 00:18:43.520 align:middle line:84%
She was able to describe
what they were doing.

00:18:43.520 --> 00:18:47.450 align:middle line:84%
She drew the pictures of the
surgical instruments and so on.

00:18:47.450 --> 00:18:50.110 align:middle line:90%


00:18:50.110 --> 00:18:53.320 align:middle line:10%
And you know, this
happens with not just

00:18:53.320 --> 00:18:56.200 align:middle line:10%
in these kinds of situations,
but all kinds of transpersonal

00:18:56.200 --> 00:19:01.330 align:middle line:10%
experiences mediate sort
of extrasensory perception,

00:19:01.330 --> 00:19:08.461 align:middle line:10%
becoming an animal, or
experiences from the past,

00:19:08.461 --> 00:19:12.730 align:middle line:10%
from historical events,
visiting the mythological realms

00:19:12.730 --> 00:19:15.950 align:middle line:10%
and having visions
from mythologies

00:19:15.950 --> 00:19:17.490 align:middle line:10%
that you never studied.

00:19:17.490 --> 00:19:20.970 align:middle line:84%
This is the Jungian idea of
the collective unconscious.

00:19:20.970 --> 00:19:24.870 align:middle line:84%
It is all well-documented
in psychedelic research

00:19:24.870 --> 00:19:29.360 align:middle line:84%
and confirmed by
holotropic breathwork.

00:19:29.360 --> 00:19:31.230 align:middle line:84%
So these kinds of
things, you know,

00:19:31.230 --> 00:19:36.330 align:middle line:84%
they ask for a radical revision
of psychiatry and psychology.

00:19:36.330 --> 00:19:40.550 align:middle line:84%
The most basic metaphysical
assumptions are wrong.

00:19:40.550 --> 00:19:43.460 align:middle line:84%
>> One in five people who
are resuscitated from cardiac

00:19:43.460 --> 00:19:47.240 align:middle line:84%
arrest are reported to have
a near-death experience.

00:19:47.240 --> 00:19:48.950 align:middle line:84%
Why would the process
of death bring

00:19:48.950 --> 00:19:51.710 align:middle line:84%
on such similar experiences
to psychedelic states

00:19:51.710 --> 00:19:53.540 align:middle line:90%
of consciousness?

00:19:53.540 --> 00:19:57.590 align:middle line:10%
One study by Jimo Borjigin
at the University of Michigan

00:19:57.590 --> 00:20:00.590 align:middle line:10%
has found that for about 30
seconds after rodent models'

00:20:00.590 --> 00:20:03.650 align:middle line:10%
breathing and heart stopped,
their brains increased

00:20:03.650 --> 00:20:08.150 align:middle line:10%
their neural activity, including
gamma waves in all of them.

00:20:08.150 --> 00:20:11.090 align:middle line:84%
Oddly enough, the activity in
different parts of the brain

00:20:11.090 --> 00:20:13.290 align:middle line:84%
became twice as
synchronized as when awake.

00:20:13.290 --> 00:20:15.890 align:middle line:90%


00:20:15.890 --> 00:20:19.790 align:middle line:84%
Cognitive Neuroscientists
John Kounios and Mark Beeman

00:20:19.790 --> 00:20:21.440 align:middle line:84%
found in their
research that what

00:20:21.440 --> 00:20:23.960 align:middle line:84%
we would term as
an aha moment has

00:20:23.960 --> 00:20:27.710 align:middle line:84%
direct correlations with gamma
wave bursts in the brain.

00:20:27.710 --> 00:20:30.850 align:middle line:84%
These bursts happen when
brain centers fire together

00:20:30.850 --> 00:20:33.560 align:middle line:84%
that have never done
so before, giving rise

00:20:33.560 --> 00:20:37.820 align:middle line:84%
to a newly integrated and
higher level of insight.

00:20:37.820 --> 00:20:41.090 align:middle line:84%
One hypothesis popularized
by Dr. Rick Strassmann

00:20:41.090 --> 00:20:43.890 align:middle line:84%
got the world thinking about
why the psychedelic compound

00:20:43.890 --> 00:20:48.700 align:middle line:84%
DMT is produced in the body
and congregates in the brain.

00:20:48.700 --> 00:20:51.910 align:middle line:10%
While the evidence of DMT being
released in dying brains is

00:20:51.910 --> 00:20:54.990 align:middle line:10%
still in question, an
article published by Juan

00:20:54.990 --> 00:21:00.460 align:middle line:10%
Acosta-Urquidi reports that
both 5-MeO and N,N-DMT caused

00:21:00.460 --> 00:21:03.250 align:middle line:10%
widespread cortical
hyper-coherence in the gamma

00:21:03.250 --> 00:21:04.720 align:middle line:10%
wave region.

00:21:04.720 --> 00:21:06.970 align:middle line:84%
While this is not
definitive proof,

00:21:06.970 --> 00:21:09.040 align:middle line:84%
Rick Strassmann gives
an insight as to why

00:21:09.040 --> 00:21:11.890 align:middle line:90%
dying brains might release DMT.

00:21:11.890 --> 00:21:14.530 align:middle line:10%
>> To protect the
body, number one,

00:21:14.530 --> 00:21:21.490 align:middle line:10%
and to kind of begin the
movement of consciousness out

00:21:21.490 --> 00:21:29.260 align:middle line:10%
of a more body-grounded state,
which occurs when you take DMT,

00:21:29.260 --> 00:21:32.500 align:middle line:10%
is you lose awareness
of your body.

00:21:32.500 --> 00:21:35.500 align:middle line:84%
So I think it would
be protective.

00:21:35.500 --> 00:21:37.540 align:middle line:84%
There are some data
from Hungary which

00:21:37.540 --> 00:21:41.530 align:middle line:84%
indicate that DMT
is what is called,

00:21:41.530 --> 00:21:45.430 align:middle line:84%
you know, neuroprotective
in conditions of low levels

00:21:45.430 --> 00:21:47.570 align:middle line:90%
of oxygen in the brain.

00:21:47.570 --> 00:21:52.120 align:middle line:84%
Which means that if
you're not providing

00:21:52.120 --> 00:21:57.370 align:middle line:84%
your brain with enough oxygen,
your nerve cells begin to die.

00:21:57.370 --> 00:22:02.650 align:middle line:84%
And DMT seems to
inhibit the bad effect

00:22:02.650 --> 00:22:06.670 align:middle line:84%
of a low level of oxygen.
It protects the brain

00:22:06.670 --> 00:22:09.310 align:middle line:90%
against low oxygen levels.

00:22:09.310 --> 00:22:12.430 align:middle line:84%
And that's why the
DMT theoretically

